text: Anne Marshall (born 1941) is a female former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== She represented England and won a gold medal in the 440 yards medley relay and silver medal in the 440 yards freestyle relay at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. She swam for the Kingston Ladies and Hampstead Swimming Clubs. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:Living people Category:English female swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in swimming Category:Commonwealth Games gold medallists for England Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for England
